---
import DearDatesLayout from "../../layouts/DearDatesLayout.astro";
import Icon from "../../components/Icon.astro";
---

<DearDatesLayout title="Privacy Policy - Dear Dates">
  <main class="w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 md:px-8 pt-12 md:pt-20 pb-24">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <a
        href="/deardates"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-gray-600 hover:text-pink-600 transition-colors mb-8"
      >
        <Icon name="arrow_back" size={20} class="text-lg" />
        <span class="font-mono text-sm uppercase">Back to Dear Dates</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <article class="max-w-none">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <h1
          class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-4"
        >
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-2">
          Dear Dates
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 font-mono text-sm uppercase">
          Last Updated: 20-01-2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Welcome to Dear Dates ("we," "our," or "the app").
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Your privacy is a core value of Dear Dates. This Privacy Policy
          explains how information is handled when you use our iOS application.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Our Privacy Commitment
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates is designed to work without collecting, tracking, or
          transmitting your personal data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          All information you enter stays on your device and remains fully under
          your control.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Information We Store (Locally on Your Device)
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Dear Dates stores all data locally on your iOS device only. We do not
          operate servers and do not sync or transmit your data.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Local Data Storage</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The app may store the following information on your device:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Profile Information:</strong> names, photos, notes, and other
              details you choose to save
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Event Information:</strong> birthdays, anniversaries, and custom
              events
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Gift Information:</strong> gift ideas, notes, and history
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>User Profile:</strong> your own profile information, if you
              create one
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>App Settings:</strong> theme preferences, accent colors, and
              notification settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>Notification Data:</strong> minimal notification information
              (event names, dates, reminder days) stored separately for notification
              delivery
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              <strong>App Preferences:</strong> language settings, onboarding completion
              status, and other preferences stored using iOS UserDefaults
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          All data is stored using SwiftData, Apple's native data persistence
          framework, and UserDefaults for app preferences.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          We do not access, transmit, back up, or sync this data to any external
          servers or cloud services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Photo Library Access
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you choose to add photos to profiles, Dear Dates may request access
          to your Photo Library.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This access:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Is requested only when you tap "Add Photo"
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Is used solely to select photos for profiles inside the app
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Copies selected photos into the app's local storage
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Does not share photos with any external services
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          You can revoke photo access at any time in iOS Settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Notifications</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates uses local notifications to remind you of upcoming events.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">These notifications:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Are scheduled and delivered entirely on your device
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Do not use servers or external services
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Do not transmit any personal data
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Can be disabled at any time in the app settings or iOS Settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Require minimal data (event names, dates, reminder days) to be
              stored separately for delivery when your device is locked
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Use iOS file protection mechanisms and are accessible only after
              your device is first unlocked following a restart
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Information We Do Not Collect
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates does not collect, transmit, or store:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Analytics data</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Usage statistics</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Third-party analytics</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Advertising identifiers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Device identifiers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Location data</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Tracking data</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Third-party tracking information</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Personally identifiable information outside your device
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          Dear Dates does not use third-party crash reporting services and does
          not collect crash data outside Apple's standard development and
          distribution tools.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Data Storage and Security
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Your data is stored locally on your device and protected by iOS
          security mechanisms.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">This means:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Your data never leaves your device through Dear Dates
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Your main database is encrypted by iOS using
              NSFileProtectionComplete and is accessible only when your device
              is unlocked
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Notification-related data is stored separately using
              NSFileProtectionCompleteUntilFirstUserAuthentication to ensure
              reminders work correctly
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Your data may be included in encrypted device backups managed by
              Apple, depending on your iOS settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Dear Dates does not access, control, or manage these backups
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          All file protection and encryption are handled by iOS and follow
          Apple's security best practices.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Data Sharing and Transmission
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates does not share, sell, rent, or transmit your data to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Third-party services</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Advertising networks</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Analytics providers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Cloud storage providers</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >External servers or databases</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The only way your data can leave your device is if you explicitly
          export it using the app's export feature.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Data Export and Deletion
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          You remain in full control of your data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">You can:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Export all your data at any time as a JSON file using the app's
              export feature
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Import previously exported data using the app's import feature
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Search and filter your data within the app (all processing is
              performed locally)
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Delete individual profiles, events, or gift ideas
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Remove all data by uninstalling the app
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Reset app preferences by uninstalling and reinstalling the app
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Third-Party Services
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates does not use third-party services that collect or transmit
          personal data.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The app uses only Apple-provided frameworks, including:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">SwiftUI</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">SwiftData</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">UserNotifications</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Photos</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Foundation</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">UserDefaults</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          No advertising, analytics, crash reporting, or cloud synchronization
          services are used.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Children's Privacy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates is not specifically designed for children under the age of
          13.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under
          13.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          If you believe that a child has provided personal information within
          the app, please contact us so we can address the issue.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          Changes to This Privacy Policy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Any changes will be reflected by updating the "Last Updated" date and
          making the revised policy available in the app or online.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">You have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-none space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Access all data stored in the app</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Export your data at any time</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed"
              >Delete your data at any time</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Control photo access via iOS Settings
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-pink-600 text-xl">•</span>
            <span class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
              Control notification permissions via app settings or iOS Settings
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you can contact
          us at:
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          <a
            href="mailto:max.qb@icloud.com"
            class="text-pink-600 hover:text-pink-700 transition-colors underline"
          >
            Email: max.qb@icloud.com
          </a>
        </p>
      </section>

      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          International Users
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          This Privacy Policy is intended to align with major privacy
          regulations, including GDPR, CCPA, and COPPA, to the extent
          applicable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Because all data is stored locally on your device and not transmitted,
          Dear Dates provides a high level of privacy protection regardless of
          your location.
        </p>
      </section>
      <section
        class="mb-8 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl p-7 shadow-sm border border-pink-100/50"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Dear Dates is built with privacy at its core.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          We don't collect your data. We don't track you. We don't share your
          information.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Your memories stay private — exactly where they belong: on your
          device.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>
</DearDatesLayout>

<style>
  /* Smooth scroll behavior */
  html {
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
  }
</style>
